# ACK-Based Communication Using ICMP (Packet Tracer)

## Objective

To study ICMP Echo Request/Reply behavior and analyze the effect of extra network hops.

## Topology

Task 1: PC1 → Switch → PC2
Task 2: PC1 → Switch1 → Switch2 → PC2

## IP Configuration

PC1: 192.168.1.1
PC2: 192.168.1.2
Subnet Mask: 255.255.255.0

## Steps

1. Connected PC1 and PC2 using one switch
2. Assigned IP addresses
3. Tested connectivity using ping
4. Observed packet flow in simulation mode
5. Added one more switch between PC1 and PC2
6. Repeated ping and observed changes

## Observation

Direct setup has fewer steps and very low delay.
Extra hop setup has more forwarding steps and slightly higher delay.

## Result

Ping was successful in both cases. Extra hop increased delay slightly.

## Conclusion

More hops increase packet travel time due to additional forwarding.

